caption: Ordered sushi on DD almost once a week for 3 months. Amazing every time.

Really enjoy the sushi, used to order it several times a week, the last few times we've ordered for delivery there's been such a long delay on the restaurant's end from the original ETA to the time the food is actually delivered that I don't know if we'll continue patronizing Umi
Disgusting costumer service. No social distance. Came to pick up my order and faced with long lane where no social distance. Had to cancel order

I’ve been a frequent customer of this place for over a year. 2 days ago I ordered sashimi deluxe, shrimp fried rice and pad thai noodle. My girlfriend and I had nausea, vomiting and diarrhea for the last 48 hours.  I don’t remember the last time I had a bad case of food poisoning like this. My stomach is still bloated and only thing I can barely keep down is tea and water. This place was one of my favorite restaurant for to-go. Will not be ordering from here again after this horrible experience. Becareful everyone
I have visited this place several times for food pick up and i had to cancel alot of times because of long time waiting .

Ordered with Uber eats and four drivers went to the restaurant to get my food, and then left because there was a problem at the restaurant. I never found out what it was because I called them multiple times and no one answered. Online it says they are open. The order was cancelled two hours later.

We met with friends at this restaurant for dinner. This spot was recommended to us by a friend.  Well, it was very successful. we were warmly welcomed by the staff members  and we had an excellent feeling. The food was just great. We had a great time and we shall definitely come back again. We recommend this place to all.
I just wanted some sushi 🍥 Sushi was terrible, not fresh at all The bag came dripping Food was tasteless Very disappointed for $53 dollars I never leave reviews but this time I felt compelled to
We love this place. Have tried a bunch of other places and always end up disappointed - “should’ve just gotten Umi.”
I love Umi, they have excellent fish and also some great vegetarian rolls including the sweet potato tempura roll. Try the sushi deluxe.
The food is excellent but the waits can be very long and they don't always give proper notice of when orders will be ready.

Amazing food coming from a sushi enthusiast. The quality and quality was way better then expected for the price they charge. It is an amazing gem and easy to overlook when passing by. Worth the time and money.
First of all it is a Chinese restaurant pretending to be Japanese. The customer service is atrocious and the food is even worse. 0/10, avoid at all cost !
Good food. Service okay. Wait times in the evening for takeout are long, but it's okay as long as you expect it.
My GrubHub delivery experience was great. The sushi special deluxe was delicious and fresh. Soup & salad was good as well.
This is the best sushi in DC.
Love this spot! Also minority owned!
Disgusting to be that blatantly discriminatory in these times. If I could give a negative star I would!

I knew they were getting some bad publicity but I figured I would try them out and give a fair review. I found the food to be average at best and over priced. Theres also what looked like bug didnt stick around to figure out. For the price, I wasn't expect drunk-night quality food. Horrible experience

I ordered sushi and sashimi for delivery and was really surprised by how fresh my food arrived. The fish was delicious, the roll was delicious they followed the requests I made thru the app.. very good!! Will order more often. Thank you!!
Really good bento lunch special, highly recommend.
Solid, reliable, delicious sushi
Excellent variety and delicious food. Service outstanding. Loved the outside patio with live music.

Ordered delivery because my usual spots were closed...the guy didn't come inside, he made me come to the car where he tried to force me to leave him a tip. I told him next time to DELIVER my food and he screamed that there wouldn't be a next time. More importantly, the food is mediocre at best.
Great service every time I go there. And I go a lot. The food is great too

Don't order from these crooks. I ordered food through UberEATS and the restaurant cancelled my order without explanation and had Uber charge me for the full order. I will never order from Umi again, nor will I use UberEATS for anything. Umi - you're horrible and karma will come back around to you.

Easily one of my favorite sushi/Japanese restaurants in DC.  Near the National Zoo by the Woodley metro this is a true neighborhood gem with great quality with fresh ingredients and they do not hold back on the meat, plus friendly staff.  I’ve been coming to this place since 2014 and each time I dine or carry out food they do not disappoint.

I like the location, close to the Marriott hotel and Metro Station. The sushi was delicious and the service was friendly. The dining area is small, so this place is good for smaller groups and individuals.

I'm staying in the Marriott for a conference and wanted an easy bite. The ordering was simple enough and they prepared everything quickly. I think the reviews might be a little generous as I saw this as really no better than grocery store sushi. My rolls were cut really thin (for seemingly no reason; the roll itself was standard size) and contained shredded lettuce which was odd/not tasty/made everything fall apart. The imitation crab and wasabi were both electric in colors, so not necessarily the best quality, but certainly passable. Taste was fine but not amazing.
Great and delicious food. Terrific and friendly service. Fair prices. Accommodating to food preferences.
Always spectacular. Never order. Just ask.

We are from out of town and staying at a nearby hotel.  We ordered takeout, and it had the neatest packaging we have ever seen!  But way better than that was the food itself.  We ordered gyoza, a few cooked sushi rolls, and chicken teriyaki.  The sauces were delicious, the food all cooked to perfection!  So flavorful, the salad greens super fresh and crispy!  The workers were also very friendly, hospitable, and polite while we waited for the food. Appeared small inside, but neat and efficient. Prices were competitive for the portions (chicken teriyaki was a full chicken breast - both sides!)  Would highly recommend to anyone!
Nice place. Good food. Reasonable price.
Always late.
Good cuisine, great location, tempura was great. What's even better is watching the staff both bicker and laugh together it's quiet and serene.

Good sushi, especially for the price. The miso soup and ginger salad were tasty as well. The restaurant is clean and nice inside, factors that should not be overlooked when considering a new sushi spot.

Started off with the dumpling soup - it was interesting but, in the future, I think I would stick with the miso.  Got the regular sushi-sashimi combo (sub a spicy tuna roll for the California roll) - nice presentation and each of the pieces was quite tasty  A little pricey but good
This was some of the best sushi I've ever had!

The food here was Amazing!! Some of the best Japanese food I have had, and I eat a lot of Japanese food. You should get the seafood spring rolls. They are different from anything I have ever had before and so so good.
Good food, good vibe

Walking around trying to find a reasonably priced meal in this area I stumbled upon Umi's. Up the stairs and into a quiet little dark sushi joint I went. I got there early before the lunch rush came in I suspect, just minutes after opening. The tables hadn't been set yet. That was how early. I ordered a Miso soup and a Fantastic roll. The soup wasn't ready so they asked if I would like my roll first. That was nice and I opted to do that. It was excellent. The special wrap and the plating made it visually so eye appealing that I felt bad eating it - to a point. Delicious. The miso was about on par with any other place and to do it again, I might opt for another starter instead. Would I recommend this place? Absolutely. Will I come here again in the future. Absolutely. Service staff were pleasant. Big bonus around here.

username: Archbishop Dr. Abrams Almasi, MDiv, DD, PhD

caption: (Translated by Google) Delicious poke  (Original) Вкусный поке
Phenomenal meal tonight and the Tempura Fried Green Tea ice cream was out of this world!!! Best Japanese food I've had in years!
Best Japanese sushi bar I have ever been. High quality with low price.

The lunch special was amazing! I loved the variety in the bento box. It was just the right size to split with my little girl. Its close proximity to the zoo made it the perfect place to fill up at for a big trek. The sushi is on another level of freshness. My daughter loves that it was on the second level which made the perfect vantage for people watching. Umi is yummy 😋
Great menu 👍
The place itself is delightful. Service was prompt and the food was EXCELLENT. Prices for lunch were very reasonable. Looking forward to eating there again.
😍 love the rolls!
tasted average. did not feel like Japanese culture at all. there was loud pop music and quite expensive.
No wheel chair accessible seen.

These people are funny. Ordered delivery through GrubHub back in April, only for them to call and cancel my order 20 minutes later. The reason provided was that it was out of the 3 mile radius range, it clearly wasn’t, only 2.5 miles from the restaurant to point of delivery. Just be honest and say you don’t want to deliver one order in traffic, no need to lie about the distance.
Super neat inside, everyone is very nice and the food was great
Got horrendous food poisoning, and pretty sure it was from a delivery order here. Had read a couple reviews warning as much and suffered the consequences of not heeding them :( beware.
Excellent, but the seating area feels a bit divey
Great fresh sushi and the tempura ice cream is some of the best in the city!
Fantastic sushi. Sit at the bar and ask for what's good.
Delicious food. Great lunch specials and delicious sushi
Delicious tidy and quick. The lunch menus aren’t very expensive and are super delicious.
Yummy vegetarian options, and fast. I recommend the veggie udon and add tofu for protein.
(Translated by Google) American food for the Japanese meal, earned  (Original) 美国分量的日餐，有赚到
bad place！ bad service
Very good, was hard to find because it's not ground level. But, I'm not from the area.
Cool place
Ordered on uberEats and was absolutely delicious. Great job on all of it. Man, those potstickers were epic! As was the pad thai
Very cozy
There is plastic in the food. Chicken is undercooked and the basil chicken has pieces of burnt “stuff” in it. Do not eat at this place.

Took my friends here for dinner and we all really enjoyed ourselves. Wide variety of dishes available, the food is excellent and the service is pretty good too. Prices are reasonable for the entrées, given the portion size. Decor could use a little work to make the place more inviting, but still provides an enjoyable experience.
Food was excellent and service was very nice ! I would love to come back again sometime !
Umi was delicious but the pics on menu didn't exist and it was cold in the place. Went in January.
Decent sushi. No bells or whistles. Mostly carryout
Decent place and the service was good, but it wasn't anything elite either.
Poke bowls were interesting and delicious, sushi was spot on. Will definitely be returning.

Kind of expensive, but there are a lot of gluten free options, and the food is absolutely delicious. I should comment that the price of the food reflects the area that you're eating in. Woodley Park in many places in DC are pretty expensive.
Best sushi I’ve ever had, incredible! If staying at the Marriott it’s a short walk and so worth it!
Very poor quality udon noodle soup.
Service is very fast. Try the white tuna, you will be surprised by the taste.

The waitresses are polite and not pushy. The place is small upstairs but nice and neat. The food however is very unlike Japanese food. We ordered beef with Japanese ginger sauce but it definitely looks and tastes like beef with broccolis Chinese style with heavy oyster sauce, and the udon tastes very much like right out from the fridge.
Solid Japanese restaurant in Woodly area.
The food was great. Had the bento box for lunch, was a good mix of food and the right quantity.
Great food and great service!
Great Poke bowls, would come here again
AMAZING sushi and sashimi!! All the food tasted completely fresh and delicious! Service was great and everyone was so polite.
I had the shrimp tempura bento lunch which proved to be a steal for $11. The tempura itself and the sides were great and the staff was very attentive.
Very good sushi for the price! It’s a very tiny restaurant, so expect some wait time.
Nice place and nice food
This was sick
high quality sushi in a minimalist setting. More of a New York style. Tons of white tuna rolls, which are hard to find and my personal favorite.

Not the best sushi, but I guess it's good for DC. There was a relatively long wait time for take-out, but the restaurant was quite busy that night. The interior was clean but a bit cramped. The staff members weren't especially nice but it seemed that they were quite overworked that evening. I didn't love the rolls that I got, but it's probably better than what you would get at most sushi places in the area. The restaurant is not wheelchair accessible. It is on the second floor.
good experience
My favorite regular sushi place in DC. Prices are decent and service is good.  Many special rolls, have rarely found any to be less than excellent.
Good food at a decent price. Small location good for a quick meal but not great for large parties.
Excellent sushi, gyoza, and miso. Prompt and friendly staff! Will return :)
Comfortable, clean, and cozy upstairs location. Come here for the lunch deals! Bento box, sushi, and nigiri options. A choice of salad or miso soup. Hot tea available. Good service.
Great food but not the best service
Wonderful little place. The people who own it are very hospitable. They made us feel at home and needless to say the food was delicious.
Go at lunch time to get the poke bowl and you can save a good $7 on your bill. It’s good. Nice upstairs location.
Great rolls and really good soup. This California girl approves!
Good sushi.
Great sushi and good service. A step above close sushi spots

This sushi is delicious! I got the BMW roll and the Godzilla roll. Both are fantastic.  Sadly, I’m probably not going to order from them again because I did not appreciate being scolded by the delivery man. He said that I should come downstairs and get my order so he doesn’t have to come up. I tipped 25% and he can’t take an elevator?! That has never happened to me with any other food delivery in DC or anywhere for that matter. Anyway, that is the only reason they are not getting 5 stars.

There is a sign out front with the restaurant's name, follow the stairs to the second floor of the building and you'll find a cozy little space with a sushi bar and a few tables for small groups (2-4 people).  We watched 3 chefs build orders behind the bar. Food was great and the space was quiet.
Late by 40 mins!! and lied about giving me a discount
Chef is not Japanese but very authentic Japanese food and sushi with great  Japanese sake selections
Got so much food for $11 during their lunch special hours. Definitely worth going.
Positives: the rolls were pretty good. Negatives: the place is terribly marked from the outside, and our server forgot part of our order..

The food was good and seemed fresh. We ordered three dishes and they took a while to come out. The service wasn't very good, the waitress was in a hurry to clear the table and took away soups and salads before they were finished. The servers seemed impatient and made me feel rushed.
Surprisingly good, nice prices.
The food is not fresh. Don't try
Definitely my to go place for sushi and sashimi. The portions are perfect and the sashimi is definitely done right.
amazing sushi! Very talented sushi chefs and great staff!
Best sushi in the neighborhood

Ordered some sushi for pick up. They said it would be ready in 10-30 min so I showed up 30 min later. Where I was ignored by the hostess for 5 min and then told to wait while she walked away. It took another 20 min sitting and waiting before I got my food. And the sushi was underwhelming. The rolls are covered in mayo sauces and the sushi cuts are poor.

Every experience here has been amazing. Love the staff; chefs are great- fun and treat the sushi just right. This place isn't over the top, snobby, or off-putting in anyway. Very welcoming, and fair priced!

Amazing sushi. So fresh, the prawns were literally trying to escape off the counter. Some of the best Hashim I've had in the city, and the mango mocha was out of this world :) I can't wait to come back here with friends!
Umi has become one of my favorites delivery and take out. Food is consistently great.
Awesome sushi!

Ordered on Grubhub for delivery. Arrived 25 minutes after the end of the delivery window and refused to deliver to my 5th floor office so I had to go down to the street. Worst of all, the yakisoba is easily the worst I've had. It doesn't appear that they use Tonkatsu in the sauce, which is the standard ingredient. Will never eat here again, do not recommend it at all.

I saw so many good ratings I gave it a try as I'm In D.C for one night and wanted to eat some good sushi. What a mistake! First of all, the food came an hour and a half after I ordered it. Still hoping they just made it, I was wrong again. It was cold as ******! I ordered the Shrimp tempura it was so cold and dry it was too gross to even slightly enjoy. I ordered a rock shrimp and if I can even explain how cold, dry, and too fried it was I would. The sushi tasted like it was leftover from the night before AND, they forgot my soda. What a terrible experience, I will not be ordering from this place ever again
The place is totally disgusting inside. And people here work having strong flue! That's crazy:( if I will not have a flue tomorrow after visiting this place - I'll be very lucky

My wife and I ordered delivery from this places Valentine's Day Feb 14, 2015.  Our order total was $50. We both ordered the Teriyaki Chicken with Tempura Shrimp.  Our order finally arrived nearly 2 hours after ordering and the chicken and shrimp was literally refrigerator temperature and was probably made when we first ordered it and been sitting on the counter top for the last 2 hours.  We were worried about food poisoning so we didn't eat our food.  The restaurant only offered 15% refund.

Fun options for vegetarians, the kind you don't find at typical "cucumber roll, asparagus roll" sushi places: a crispy fried mushroom and cream cheese roll that was amazing, a sweet tofu and avocado roll that was nearly as amazing, and a dragon roll with asparagus and sweet potato topped with avocado that I sincerely regret not trying. Climb the short flight of stairs and be rewarded with a much more authentic experience than the dollar-sushi place a few doors down!
I have never been here before, but if it says Japanese grill, I'll love it. I will give it 5 stars since Japanese food is da bomb. (licks lips).                :)-

I'm a little particular about my sushi and although it's not the best, it's good.  My order taste fresh, but for some reason just didn't wow me...with the exception of my tamago and unagi orders.  They were perfect.  I ordered through GrubHub because I was knee-deep in the weeds with work.  Nevertheless, I did not like I had to come outside of my building to pick up my order.  In the driver's defense, there were signs that said "No Parking", but was still a bit annoyed as I had to go downstairs twice as he wasn't there when he called me the first time.  I might be tempted again.
Delicious, classy, clean, & affordable

Ordered it through grub hub because I was too lazy to drive and trying to recover. Fish was good and fresh and the price is consistent with isn't the norm for dc. The food arrived promptly and everything was there. My only snub is a common occurrence when you order spicy tuna rolls, they blend the fish. Not a fan of that because you know it's the scraps. Otherwise meal was good and will have to eat at the restaurant at some point. Good spot and I'm super particular about my sushi that I drove to Baltimore for my favorite sushi joint versus eating it in dc
Really great quality sushi. Had really good sea urchin sushi (really big pieces too). Special rolls were great. Definitely better than nearby Tono sushi.

A decent place that is tucked away on the 2nd floor and is basically hidden in this forest of restaurants on Connecticut.  Well worth a visit as the food was pretty good in my opinion, and quite good value and price for Japanese.  Also I found the decor a bit nicer than usual for the area.

This place is an absolute hidden gem! The sushi is fantastic and you can sit at the bar and watch the chefs make it all right there. The service isn't anything to write home about, but you never have to wait. Very punctual, if anything. I come here at least once a week to try a new roll. Sometimes the chef will even surprise me with something new. Absolutely must go!
